# Code Review Process

## Overview

Our code review process ensures code quality, knowledge sharing, and maintainability.

## Pull Request Template

```markdown
## Description

[Description of changes]

## Type of Change

- [ ] Bug fix
- [ ] New feature
- [ ] Breaking change
- [ ] Documentation update

## Testing

- [ ] Unit tests added/updated
- [ ] Integration tests added/updated
- [ ] E2E tests added/updated
- [ ] Manual testing completed

## Checklist

- [ ] Code follows style guidelines
- [ ] Tests passing
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Self-review completed
- [ ] No unnecessary dependencies added
```

## Review Process

### 1. Preparation

#### Author Responsibilities

- Create feature branch
- Write clear commit messages
- Follow coding standards
- Add/update tests
- Update documentation

#### PR Requirements

- Clear description
- Linked issues
- Test coverage
- Documentation
- Clean commits

### 2. Review

#### Reviewer Responsibilities

- Code correctness
- Design quality
- Test coverage
- Documentation
- Performance impact

#### Review Focus Areas

- Business logic
- Error handling
- Security concerns
- Performance
- Maintainability

### 3. Feedback

#### Providing Feedback

- Be constructive
- Explain reasoning
- Suggest solutions
- Share knowledge
- Be timely

#### Feedback Categories

- Critical (must fix)
- Major (should fix)
- Minor (nice to fix)
- Nitpick (optional)

### 4. Resolution

#### Addressing Feedback

- Acknowledge feedback
- Discuss alternatives
- Make changes
- Request re-review
- Update tests

#### Merging Requirements

- All comments resolved
- CI/CD passing
- Required approvals
- Documentation updated
- Tests passing

## Best Practices

### For Authors

#### Code Quality

- Follow style guide
- Write clear code
- Add proper tests
- Update documentation
- Self-review first

#### PR Size

- Keep PRs small
- Single responsibility
- Clear scope
- Logical commits
- Easy to review

#### Communication

- Clear descriptions
- Proactive updates
- Timely responses
- Ask for clarification
- Be open to feedback

### For Reviewers

#### Review Approach

- Be thorough
- Be timely
- Be constructive
- Share knowledge
- Focus on important issues

#### Code Analysis

- Logic correctness
- Error handling
- Performance
- Security
- Maintainability

#### Testing Review

- Test coverage
- Test quality
- Edge cases
- Error scenarios
- Performance tests

## Review Checklist

### Code Quality

- [ ] Follows style guide
- [ ] Clear and maintainable
- [ ] No code smells
- [ ] Proper error handling
- [ ] Efficient implementation

### Testing

- [ ] Sufficient coverage
- [ ] Edge cases covered
- [ ] Error scenarios tested
- [ ] Performance tested
- [ ] Integration tested

### Security

- [ ] Input validation
- [ ] Authentication/Authorization
- [ ] Data protection
- [ ] Error handling
- [ ] Security headers

### Documentation

- [ ] Code comments
- [ ] API documentation
- [ ] README updates
- [ ] Change log
- [ ] Migration guide (if needed)

